description: Probably from a North Germanic source, compare dialectal Norwegian penn (“peen”), Danish pind (“peg”), German Pinne (“the peen of a hammer”), Old Swedish pæna (“to pound iron with a hammer”).

entries.meaning: The (often spherical) end of the head of a hammer opposite the main hammering end.

verbs.description: peen (third-person singular simple present peens, present participle peening, simple past and past participle peened)

entries.meaning: To shape metal by striking it, especially with a peen.

description: Clipping of penis, with the spelling changed to maintain the original pronunciation.
